{
  "texts": [
    "Style-based methods heavily rely on the content of information for their effectiveness.",
    "They can be highly effective in the early detection of disinformation and play a crucial role in preventing its further dissemination on social networks.",
    "However, if the writing style undergoes significant changes, the efficiency of the model may decrease.",
    "In other words, detecting disinformation based on style becomes a cat-andmouse game, as adversaries can adapt and modify their writing style to evade detection.",
    "Every successful detection in the process inspires countermeasures by the disseminators of disinformation (Zhou and Zafarani 2020)."
  ]
}